                                                                                          Introduction to EDR — Task-Wise Answers

Task 2 – What is an EDR?
• Feature giving full context: Visibility
• Process that spawned sc.exe: cmd.exe

Task 3 – Beyond the Antivirus
• Analogy for AV: Immigration Check
• Hijacked legitimate process: svchost.exe
• Solution that might mark this as clean: Antivirus

Task 4 – How an EDR works?
• EDR component collecting telemetry: Agent
• EDR agent also known as: Sensor

Task 5 – EDR Telemetry
• Telemetry for detecting C2: Network Connections
• Windows configuration stored in: Registry

Task 6 – Detection and Response Capabilities
• Feature that identifies malicious behaviours: IOC Matching

Task 7 – Investigate an Alert on EDR
• Tool launched by CMD.exe: CURL.exe
• Path to downloaded malware: C:\Users\Public\install.exe
• Path of suspicious syncsvc.exe: C:\Users\haris.khan\AppData\Local\Temp\syncsvc.exe
• URL for exfiltration attempt: https://files-wetransfer.com/upload/session/ab12cd34ef56/dump_2025.dmp
